review_blob:
Fuller's London Pride is a quintessential English Ale; malty, bitter, slightly hoppy and dangerously drinkable. Pours an apple juice, copper-color with a thin head. Aromas mostly of malt, apple and pear. Flavours the same. Thin mouthfeel, refreshing carbonation. It could use more hops, it's slightly too sweet. Overall, it makes me feel like I'm in the pub, and that's a good thing.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Pours a large white head, golden honey color. Significant lacing as head bubbles down. Hoppy, bitter, refreshing, delicious.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Tastes of grassy, beer flavoured soda water. A very light yeast-pear tinge that is pleasant, but far too subtle to matter. This is not what beer should be. It's a low calorie marketing gimmick, and a drink that was never intended to taste good.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: 6-pack of bottles in St. Louis, MO. Pours black, with an off-cream, 1-inch head. Nice velvet mouthfeel. Vanilla works well. However, it finishes flat, and slightly watery, just as other reviewers have pointed out. This beer needs more hops. The flavour is not very complex or very satisfying. A slightly above average porter. ---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Pours light, honey-golden. 1-inch white head with lacing. Bouquet of hops, fruit, pineapple. Crisp, hoppy and citrus flavour. A good winter IPA. Very drinkable.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Pours no head, apple juice color. Super sweet, bourbon, rubbing alcohol. Not a good beer.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Bottle from Falls Liquor, Minneapolis, MN. Bottled in 2012. Pours a brown, red, caramel-toffee. 1/4" head. Christmas flavour baby!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

6 pack of cans from Falls Liquor, Minneapolis, MN. Pours a cloudy, dark apple juice color, almost grapefruit. Thin, carbonated mouthfeel. Slight taste of pumpkin pie. Overall, a very drinkable beer, but slightly watery; could use more hops. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Pours a beautiful copper color with a small wispy head. Slight hops with a background of clove, cinnamon, brown sugar and slight pine. Great balance. 7.5% alcohol sits in the background. A nice Christmas beer.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Bottle from Total Wine, Vegas. Whoa, huge flavour. Pours thick black with a massive brown head. Head remains at 1cm through half a glass. Malty, hoppy, chocolate, finishes boozy, hoppy, metallic. This is an over-the-top beer, just as it claims to be.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Beer Valley Black Flag Imperial Stout

review_blob:
Dark coffee colored pour. Little to no head. Smells of coffee, bourbon. Tastes of chocolate, bourbon, coffee, vanilla, prunes. Silky, carbonated mouthfeel. At 14.2% this is a bodacious beer.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Beautiful light golden pour with a fluffy white head. Ridiculous balance. Refreshing and drinkable. This would be my ideal beer on warm summer evening. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Great hoppy, citrus aroma. Beautiful, golden honey color. Huge flavour of grapefruit and hops.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Fruity bouquet of black cherries. Pours a dark brown. First taste is thin, fruity, hoppy. Flavour deepens as you drink, but remains a little too jumbled.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
